tests.title: should create an account for the application
tests.fullTitle: Authenthication should create an account for the application

tests.title: should login into the application
tests.fullTitle: Authenthication should login into the application
tests.code:
_auth.default.login("pain@mail.com", "P@$$w0rd!");
cy.url().should('eq', 'https://ui-automation-camp.vercel.app/products'); // asserts that the user is taken to the products page after login

tests.title: should not login with incorrect password
tests.fullTitle: Authenthication should not login with incorrect password
tests.code:
_auth.default.login("ellen@mail.com", "P@$$w0rd"); // attempts to login with an incorrect password

cy.get(_auth.default.errorMessage).should('have.text', 'Wrong email or password.'); // asserts that the user is prompted with an error message

tests.title: should not login with incorrect email
tests.fullTitle: Authenthication should not login with incorrect email
tests.code:
_auth.default.login("ell77en@mail.com", "P@$$w0rd!"); // attempts to login with an incorrect email 

cy.get(_auth.default.errorMessage).should('have.text', 'Wrong email or password.'); // asserts that the user is prompted with an error message

tests.title: should not login with invalid email
tests.fullTitle: Authenthication should not login with invalid email
tests.code:
_auth.default.login("e7en@mail", "P@$$w0rd!"); //attempts to login with an invalid email

cy.get(_auth.default.invalidCredError).should('have.text', 'Email is invalid'); // asserts that the user is prompted with an error message

tests.title: should not create an account for the application without password
tests.fullTitle: Authenthication should not create an account for the application without password
tests.code:
_auth.default.signUpWithoutPassword('ellen@mail.com'); // attempts to create an account without a password

cy.get(_auth.default.invalidCredError).should('have.text', "Password can't be blank"); // asserts that the user is prompted with an error message
